<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,152,1944]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,312,1765,1791]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. Large, dark brown species with a long robust, flattened proboscis, unusually large flagellum with punctations, mesonotum with a wide dark longitudinal stripe divided anteriorly, a dark elongate spot on each side, and golden yellow tomentum laterally, largely yellow microtrichose wings, brown beyond base of cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[214,222,1894,1908]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">4</subScript>
; presence of a stout black, posteroventral bristle on the apical 1/3 of the mesothoracic femur; and terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[285,427,1918,1944]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 41–47" captionStart-1="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId-0="18.[150,268,1749,1773]" captionStartId-1="19.[151,276,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1431,198,1719]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1428,693,1895]" captionTargetId-0="figure-196@18.[151,1436,197,1729]" captionTargetId-1="figure-293@19.[151,1436,665,1905]" captionTargetPageId-0="18" captionTargetPageId-1="19" captionText-0="FIGURES 41–47. Longibeccus imperator (Oldroyd), male, wing and terminalia. 41. Left wing. Figures 42–44. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 45. Gonostylus; 46–47. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; distph=disti phallus; epand=epandrium; ep iph=epiphallus; goncx=gon ocoxit e; hypd=hyp andrium; pvapod=posteroventral apodeme." captionText-1="FIGURES 48–51. Longibeccus imperator (Oldroyd), female terminalia. 48–49. Dorsal and ventral views; 50. Spermathecae; 51. Genital fork. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; tg8= tergite 8, tg9=tergite 9; st7=sternite 7, st8=sternite 8." pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 42–51</figureCitation>
) characterize the species.
</paragraph>
